[src:slf4j-logging-java/java-programming-language] JavaFX is a software platform for creating and delivering desktop applications, as well as rich web applications that can run across a wide variety of devices.
[src:slf4j-logging-java/java-programming-language] JavaFX is intended to replace Swing as the standard graphical user interface (GUI) library for Java SE, but since JDK 11 JavaFX has not been in the core JDK and is instead available as a separate module.
